CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "Cute 'Honeybunnies' Paraded... and captured the hears of everyone at the fashion show at A. Leo Weil School. Wearing perky spring outfits with sparkling smiles on their faces, some came out in pairs, as a single, or in one instance, as a trio.  Left to right: Duane and Delmonte Miller... "
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Duane Miller, and Delmonte Miller modeling floral dress with tied hat, and holding house shaped purse, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil school for Easter fashion show
